review_blob: It is what it is.. A very light summer lager.. But when you are out in the sun I dont want something heavy. Just want a thirst quencher.. Best in the can with salt on the rim and a lime stuffed inside.. Ill take it over Corona any day....

Aroma was a bit on the skunky side. Pours golden with a decent head, Tastes bitter and lingers.  If my mouth is burning because of the Thai food I will drink it  but other wise No desire to try it again..
Pours a light gold color. Aroma is tangy to sweet. Tastes just like it smells with a little bitterness.. But goes down easy and is good with Hot foods..

My favorite Hefe. Pours light gold almost yellow with a good head. Mild tangy aroma. Fresh lemon taste but not too sweet.Goes down real easy and clean. Another great food beer as it is not too filling and goes well with almost everything..

Got it in cans.. Reminds me a lot of Coors. Golden yellow with a slightly bitter aftertaste.. Slightly salty maybe thatswhy it goes pretty good with fish.. Not great but better than the average lite style beer.

Strong... Pours deep heavy chocolate. tastes heavy of vanilla and Molasses with a eye opening bourbon kicker.. Not for the faint of heart.. After just one pour you sure feel the warmth of that alcohol content.
Decent white beer. Nothing to really grab on to though.. Some hints of fruit and wheat. Goes down smooth and isnt heavy. No lingering aftertaste...

Solid beer. Aroma is on the sweet side but not fruity. POurs a light golden color with a medium head.  Tastes lemony to the tart side. Nice and even going down with a smooth finish. It is definitely my go to beer if nothing else is interesting. Not filling which i Like.

Pours a rich golden hue with a good head. Smells almost  pungent with different fruits and corriander, The aroma lingers giving you time to debate what all is in there. There is a lot going on in this beer.  It was medium body and I was left with a little aftertaste.. Took some getting used to but the more I drank the more I liked it .

Aroma was fresh almost zesty. Appearance was cloudy with not much head. The body was medium, almost creamy,with average carbonation. Taste was a smooth even mix of  light sweetness, With a tangy lemon kicker. And no heavy after taste or feeling which I really like..
